This is the new documentation root. Please do not distribute files from this
repository without approval from Akopia.

To set up your SDF environment do the following:

(1) install SDF using

    perl -MCPAN -e '"install I/IA/IANC/sdf-2.001.tar.gz"'

(2) hack PERLSITELIB/sdf/macros.pl by adding this line

1093a1094
>         push(@text, "!inherit \"look/$value\"") if($name eq 'OPT_LOOK');

(3) create PERLSITELIB/sdf/home/look/akopia and add the files from the akopia
    directory

(4) if you'll be making the dev_html target (if you're generating the
    Akopia Developer Resource documentation pages), make this patch to
    PERLSITELIB/sdf/tohtml.pl:

*** tohtml.pl	Mon May 24 04:44:27 1999
--- /usr/lib/perl5/site_perl/5.6.0/sdf/tohtml.pl	Tue Jan 16 16:01:55 2001
***************
*** 516,521 ****
--- 516,528 ----
      else {
          $para = &_HtmlParaText($para_text);
      }
+     if ($SDF_USER::var{ITL_ESCAPE}) {
+         # escape ITL [tags] and __VAR__, @_VAR_@, and @@VAR@@ so HTML
+         # can be served through Akopia Interchange
+         $para =~ s/\[/&#91;/g;
+         $para =~ s/_(_[A-Za-z0-9]\w*?[A-Za-z0-9]__)/&#95;$1/g;
+         $para =~ s/@(([_@])([A-Za-z0-9]\w*?[A-Za-z0-9])\2@)/&#64;$1/g;
+     }
  
      # Add surrounding lines for a note
      $note_line_width = 80;              # Hard-coded for now
